# MAESTRO - CONSTITUTION-002

# Constitutional Glossary

**Status:** RATIFIED

---

## Constitutional Purpose

The Constitutional Glossary establishes the authoritative meanings of constitutional terms used throughout the MAESTRO Constitution.

Unless expressly defined otherwise, these definitions shall apply consistently across the constitutional repository.

---

## Authoritative Definitions

### Amendment

A formally ratified modification to the Constitution made in accordance with established constitutional procedures.

---

### Baseline

The complete body of ratified constitutional authority that serves as the official constitutional reference point.

---

### Constitution

The supreme governing authority of MAESTRO consisting of all ratified constitutional artifacts.

---

### Constitutional Authority

Authority derived directly from the Constitution through formal ratification.

---

### Constitutional Corpus

The complete collection of ratified constitutional doctrines and constitutional records.

---

### Constitutional Doctrine

A ratified constitutional principle establishing enduring governance authority.

---

### Constitutional Integrity

The preservation of constitutional accuracy, consistency, authenticity, and authority.

---

### Constitutional Repository

The official repository containing the authoritative constitutional records of MAESTRO.

---

### Constitutional Steward

An individual entrusted with preserving, maintaining, and protecting constitutional authority.

---

### Constitutional Continuity

The uninterrupted preservation of constitutional authority across time and institutional development.

---

### Governance

The constitutional framework through which institutional authority is exercised.

---

### Institution

The enduring organisational entity governed by the Constitution.

---

### Ratification

The formal act by which constitutional authority is granted to an artifact.

---

### Repository

The official collection of constitutional artifacts maintained under constitutional stewardship.

---

### Stewardship

The ongoing responsibility to preserve constitutional authority, continuity, and institutional integrity.

---

## Interpretive Authority

Where ambiguity exists regarding constitutional terminology, this glossary shall be regarded as the primary constitutional reference unless superseded by a later ratified constitutional definition.

---

## Constitutional Consistency

The Constitutional Glossary exists to promote consistent constitutional interpretation throughout the MAESTRO constitutional repository.

